                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Italy/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-27T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. Department’s 85, June 20, 5 p.m.<note n="28" xml:id="d131fn28">Not
                        printed.</note> Foreign Office accepts proposal to send delegation to
                    discuss war debts and requests Embassy to communicate most opportune time for
                    arrival of delegates at Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
